comments.body:
Currently, sendFeedbacktoServer is NOT used on 1.3 and 2.0 both environments.

I checked the json data which result from same behavior on both environments, it called from a suspicious number and it sets to the black list.
Json data posted by sendBatchFeedbacktoServer are following.
By the way, the server returns code 200 for post data on 2.0.

|Name|Value(1.3)|Value(2.0)|Note|
|MN|260|260| |
|AV|1.3.4.0|2.0.0.100| |
|OV|27|27| |
|MC|310|310| |
|ID|1c69ddb3-d6ec-371c-b5fd-9f519747bce3|6bd86a8b4c00a58c| |
|AID|905|905| |
|FB[0]| | | |
|R|ATTENTION|ATTENTION| |

|UC| | | |
|CT|02-19-2018 15:00:10|02-19-2018 14:36:15| |
|D|0|0| |
|N|05023456789|05023456789| |
|RT|02-19-2018 15:00:12|02-19-2018 14:36:16| |
|C| | | |
|CG|N/A| |It means User Category|
|FB[1]| | | |
|R|ATTENTION|ATTENTION| |
|US|Low|Low| |
|DS|Third Party Alert List|Third Party Alert List| |
|UC|Add to Denial|Add to Denial| |
|CT|02-19-2018 15:00:10|0|This is Bug on 2.0|
|D|0|0| |
|N|05023456789|05023456789| |
|RT|02-19-2018 15:00:29|02-19-2018 14:36:21| |
|C|Call History|Call History| |
|CG|N/A| |It means User Category|

I think there're 2 points:
# "CG" exists on 2.0 only. Should we remove this?
# When user added to black list, "CT" changes to 0. I think this is a bug.
 
* About CT bug:
 ** In AbsCallLogFragment.confirmToAdd, mStartTime is not set value.
 ** I can fix it like this:
 ** mStartTime = ((AbsCallLogAdapter)getListAdapter()).getItemStartTime(position);

What was the status code when ANC2.0 send feedback to back end.
And would you also check the back end behavior from following site.
Report portal: http://apps.liveqa.mcafeemobilesecurity.com/FCPReports
Log: http://apps.liveqa.mcafeemobilesecurity.com/logs/

Status code means HTTP status code 200 = Success, and the server replied nothing.
And, I confirmed Report portal and found both(1.3 and 2.0) result. please see attached screenshot.
(I don't understand where should I see the Log server...)
Check the log of "FCP > HTML > log > htm > log.htm".

h2. Structure Description - How to store an event to the db
 * uses following functions
 ** FeedbackSync.saveFeedback()
 ** FeedbackUtils.saveFeedbackForServer()
 ** FeedbackUtils.formatFeedbackToSavetoDB()
 *** This function is used at FeedbackUtils internal only.
 ** FeedbackUtils.formatLFeedbackToSavetoDB()
 * at FeedbackUtils.prepareFeedbackString(), each parameters changes to JsonObject.
 * handled parameters are following:
 ** RESULT
 ** USER_SETTING
 ** DECISION_SOURCE
 ** USER_CLASSIFICATION
 ** CALL_START_TIME
 ** DURATION
 ** INCOMING_NUMBER
 ** REGISTRATION_TIME
 ** CHANNEL
 ** CATEGORY
 ** COMMENTS
 * note: if a parameter is null, it's NOT added to the JsonObject. Only COMMENTS, it's NOT added if it's also empty.

h2. Structure Description - How to send to the server
 * SyncFeedbackThread manages the posting process.
 * At last, WebServiceCallUtil.sendBatchFeedbacktoServer posts directly.
 ** When the function is called, it makes Header block (6 parameters from MN to AID).
 ** Feedback list in the argument is inserted as the children in "FB" array.

h2. Structure Description - How to store an event to the db (v1.3)
 * It's basically same as v2.0
 * Of course, it doesn't handle CATEGORY and COMMENTS.

h2. Structure Description - How to send to the server (v1.3)
 * SyncFeedbackThread manages the posting process.
 * However, v2.0 is managed by ScheduleManager in SyncFeedbackThread class, but v1.3 is managed by itself thread.
 * After the communication process is kicked, it seems almost same as v2.0.

We decided to remove the code related to following two keys.
* CATEGORY
* COMMENTS

I found some different points from v1.3. 
h2. Definitely bug.
 * CallLog
 ** When source is "User Denial List", "DS" has a value "User Allow List".
 * ActivityLog
 ** ANC doesn't post CT and D values for activities in Call History.

h2. Different behavior from v1.3
 * CallLog
 ** When source is "Yellow page", ANC posts a report as "YELLOW_PAGE".
 * ActivityLog
 ** Generally, ANC often posts different "C" value from v1.3.

 

For details, please see ANC v2.0Feedbacklog.xlsx, Yellow cells are different points from v1.3.

This must be fix before Final release.
(Fix must be included in market app)
Changbin as a temporary assignee.
We MUST fix/verify this bug until Pre-Final release.
